The Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) said it has suspended the presentation of certificates of return to candidates of the All Progressives Congress (APC) in Zamfara state as a result of the judgement of the Appeal Court in Sokoto. The Court of Appeal, sitting in Sokoto State set aside judgement of the Zamfara High Court which paved way for the APC to field candidates in the 2019 general elections. “Breaking: INEC has been served with the judgment of the Court of Appeal Sokoto concerning the sponsoring of candidates by the APC in Zamfara and is studying same,” the electoral commission tweeted. “Consequently, the presentation of Certificates of Return for the Zamfara Governorship and State House of Assembly scheduled for Wednesday 27th March 2019 has been suspended,” the commission posted on its verified Twitter account.  INEC halts presentation of Certificates of Return to Zamfara Governor-elect, others Zamfara APC: Court of Appeals lifts court order on candidates' list BREAKING: INEC clears Zamfara APC to participate in 2019 elections